OL,3,CThe quiet town at the centre of a
OL,4,Cmulti-million pound criminal conspiracy
OL,6,FThey accepted cash and money paid into
OL,7,Fbank accounts; home improvements were
OL,8,Fpaid for; they had the use of prestige
OL,9,Fcars, holidays and luxury hotel rooms.
OL,11,FThe payments - which came from Priddy
OL,12,FEngineering Limited and RK Civil
OL,13,FEngineering - were covered up with
OL,14,Ffalse references and fake wage slips.
OL,16,FHeyward spent his bribery money on
OL,17,Fgambling and drugs; the Bakers spent
OL,18,Ftheirs on climbing the property ladder.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/20
