OL,3,CThe quiet town at the centre of a
OL,4,Cmulti-million pound criminal conspiracy
OL,6,FMark Baker was appointed head of
OL,7,Fprojects and tasked with delivering
OL,8,Fthe district heating project for E.ON,
OL,9,Fwith Matthew Heyward employed as a
OL,10,Fquantity surveyor, responsible for
OL,11,Fsigning off the work.
OL,13,FPriddy Engineering Ltd was controlled
OL,14,Fby Andrew Blunsdon, who paid bribes to
OL,15,Fboth Baker and Heyward.
OL,17,FRK Civil Engineering Ltd (RKC) was run
OL,18,Fby Richard King and Timothy Patterson.
OL,19,FBank accounts linked to the two paid
OL,20,Fmore than #1.5million to Baker and
OL,21,FHeyward.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/20
